#29212
wretchglow spinosaurid silhouette bioluminescent~
a wretchglow~
<122>You see a huge spinosaurid silhouette lit by a sickly bioluminescent lure.<0>
~
The wretchglow is a magical, deep-water spinosaurus variant known as “the Last 
Light”, a name earned from the ghostly glow that hangs before it in the 
darkness. It haunts submerged caves and lightless channels, using its 
bioluminescence to attract curious or desperate prey before closing with 
terrible speed and razor-sharp teeth. Its glow is beautiful from a distance, 
but once the great shape behind it emerges from the murk the watcher 
understands what has found them.
~
