An anguillian glides through the deep water, its six-foot eel-like body covered 
in mottled brown scales and ending in a flat, finned tail. Short legs and wide 
six-toed feet tuck beneath it, while two upper appendages end in hard bony 
pincers. Its blunt, eyeless, jawless face is dominated by a circular mouth 
