#29208
abyssal marrowfruit~
an abyssal marrowfruit~
A soft, pearl-white abyssal marrowfruit pulses faintly with blue light.~
~
26 64 1|16384
70~ regenerate~ ~ ~
1 0 0
E
abyssal marrowfruit~
The abyssal marrowfruit grows in clusters along the bones of ancient 
things that sank too deep to rot. Each fruit is no larger than a 
clenched fist, pale and translucent, with slow threads of blue-green 
light moving beneath its skin like veins. When split open, it 
releases a faint mineral sweetness and a shimmer of silvery sap that 
clings to wounds, sealing torn flesh with an itching, unnatural speed. 
Deep-sea scavengers will fight viciously over even a bruised specimen, 
and divers whisper that eating too much of it does not merely heal the 
body, but encourages it to remember older, stranger shapes.
~

